##After the city was sealed, an AIDS patient joined the loving motorcade | sandwich

WECHAT china30s

Feature description, a platform that encourages you to write about your life. Founded in March 2011, it has a sandwich writing school and a media platform, China Sandwich, at the same time, we are committed to applying the story to cross-border product design, urban culture excavation, exhibition fair, space creation and other three-dimensional field.

By Wu Nan

Song Yao's "premature" (Wuhan dialect for breakfast) was cancelled along with the closure of the city on January 23.

From that day on, 10:30 am and 11 am became Song Yao's wake-up time. "I don't want to go to work either. I get up too early and feel very bored at home. I'd better get up late and eat when I get up. "

After washing up, my mother had already made lunch. A family of three born and raised in Wuhan, even the Stir-fried tomato and scrambled eggs, will put a bit of pepper to borrow flavor.

After every meal, Song went to the bathroom to "brush his teeth. ". At first, mom and dad feel very surprised, "in the outside work for nearly four years, after returning to Wuhan, how to still have such a habit of brushing teeth after meals? "

Song Yao would never tell his family. He is a drug has been more than two years of AIDS patients. In recent years, he has sought to reduce the side effects of taking anti-hiv drugs, dizziness and a sense of hangover, some of the first-line drug combination Tiera, which is free in the country, has been replaced with Welling, "dizziness is no more, but also trouble, this drug must be taken with meals, otherwise there is no effect. " So every day after lunch, he will go to the bathroom to "brush teeth. ".

1

On Jan. 22, Song Yao, 39, was not conscious of wearing a mask. He is a heavy smoker. It is inconvenient for him to smoke if he wears a mask. No one could tell, because Song Yao, a loud man who spends most of his days traveling, dealing with migrant workers and even shouting at them, was suffering from a chronic illness that required lifelong medication.

That day, Song Yao drove to the outskirts of Wuhan and took his parents to the house he bought. This is also his habit of returning to Wuhan for the past two years. He spent every New Year in the house he bought. "I told my parents that the downtown area was quite lively. People in Wuhan love to be lively, " Song Yao said with a smile in his voice, "In fact, I have my own plan. Instead of going home with a few days' supply of medicine, I'll find out if I'm not careful. I'd rather be at home. My Mom and dad really don't have the habit of rummaging around. "

Chinese New Year, for people infected with AIDS, is the "clearance. ". Even if there is no epidemic this time, ordinary days, infected people have to find ways to hide the drug in the side, on time to take, not to mention home for the New Year. Even the staff of the CDC or doctors at the designated hospitals will tell us before each Chinese New Year, "Ten million more take a month's medicine, go home New Year do not know what will encounter. " But not all the infected dare to take more than half a month of medicine home. The appearance of the anti-hiv drug is hard to forget at a glance, the color of the sugar coating is rare pink, blue and yellow (the same as the color of some domestic drugs) , and the size of the pill also makes people feel puzzled, what medicine can be bigger than the good store piece even on a circle? While half a month's supply is more than enough for a simple vitamin pill bottle, no infected person is willing to take such a risk, leaving family members with unnecessary doubts and endless trouble to follow up.

"Too many drugs, it is easy to be found, " said one person who declined to give his name and address. The patient came back to Wuhan from Northeast China for the Spring Festival. He brought only seven days' worth of medicine with him. "It was expected that he would be back at the latest on the sixth day of the Lunar New Year. " But he did not expect that after the order to close the city of Wuhan on January 23 was issued, "The train station, the highway, the airport are not immediately closed, incredibly still have a few hours to leave! " In his view, this is a silver lining.

Shortly after 6 a.m. on Jan. 23, he said to his parents, "I have to go. " His parents objected, "it's just a city shutdown. Why are you panicking? There are so many New Year's items in the family, and you have food and drink, so you can stay in Wuhan. "

If not infected with AIDS, he would have stayed, "but now is not the same ah! The drug is life. I stay, once the drug ran out, life is gone. "

The road out of Wuhan is not easy. The patient could not buy a direct flight back to the northeast, and he was afraid to go to a first-tier city like Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Shenzhen. "None of us had any symptoms. " But he was still nervous. first-tier cities must be strictly controlled, so he decided to book a high-speed train ticket from Wuhan to Nanjing, and then from Nanjing back to the northeast. Instead, he found a self-driving car from Wuhan to Nanjing. "I even wanted to go to Henan, but luckily I found a car to Nanjing. "

The patient friend has been urging the owner to pick him up a little faster, while his parents at the last moment to see his son's insistence, agreed, although do not understand why this is.

It was not the first time that a patient had been away on New Year's Day, but it was the first time he had left home less than a day before the Spring Festival. "It wasn't until I got on the highway that I was relieved, but my mom kept calling me, and I kept telling myself not to cry. " When I got back, the patient was in a state of self-isolation, and everything was fine.

And many of those infected are not as clean as this patient. In Wuhan, a sprawling city on the new frontier, many people have canceled their plans to go home for the New Year and are returning tickets, buying new year goods and adapting to life with fewer and fewer cars on the streets.

For many chronic patients, the suspension of public transportation and isolation at home means that once the drugs in hand to control the disease run out, they face withdrawal and withdrawal, and the consequences are not as simple as not getting the disease under control, more likely means the failure of the drug, drug resistance.

Such chronic diseases include many kinds, AIDS is one of them. For people living with AIDS, drug resistance may mean that a certain or even a certain series of, the same pharmacological drug failure. This combination of drugs on the original choice is not much AIDS patients, like a gun to the temple.

2

Over the next few days, Song felt lucky. On my way to pick up mom and dad, I stopped by a pharmacy on the outskirts of town, and I went in and bought six bags of disposable surgical masks. And then, about a week ago, he went to Wuhan State Hospital to pick up his medicine.

"The city was closed at the beginning, and it was not easy to stay at home all day. " Shortly before 10 p.m. on January 23, Song received a message from a friend of a colleague asking for help, "It was a female doctor, a few years younger than me, and the hospital asked them to return to their posts urgently, but there was no taxi, Didi or anything like that. " The city had fallen into a strange silence. Lights are on in every home, almost everyone is waiting in front of the television, more and more medical staff have become "retrograde. ".

The lady doctor's home is in Hankou. The drive from Panlongcheng to Hankou, which normally takes 40 or 50 minutes, was an excruciatingly slow half-hour. Song Yao originally more introverted silence, in the face of female doctors, do not know what to say. The woman doctor has been answering messages on her cell phone, saying she's on her way to the hospital. Soong drove for another half hour to take the woman to the hospital. Before getting off the bus, the female doctor told Song Yao, "the mask should be changed regularly, and you should wear goggles! " After returning home, Song Yao's heart was quite proud, "It never occurred to me that an hiv-infected person like myself would one day be able to go to the doctor and contribute to the hospital. "

As song parked his car in an underground garage and headed upstairs to his home, he had no idea that he would need to pick up and drop off members of his aids-infected community over the next few days. Song prefers to refer to them as "sick friends. " "In the past, I didn't know any of them. I didn't want to know them, and I didn't want anyone to know that I had the disease. "

On the advice of a female doctor, Song drove to a still open sports equipment the next day and bought three goggles for the family, each costing 199 yuan. Less than an hour after returning home in the afternoon, he received a call from a doctor recommended by a friend. "Can you take me to the hospital? " Song Yao was a little surprised. He did not expect the doctors in Wuhan to face the city is also so helpless, even if want to go to the hospital to work, also can not ride a bicycle to Wuhan, after all, is a mountainous area. But when the most basic traffic is not able to guarantee, how to arrive at the scene, has become a real problem. In fact, the follow-up trip to the public has become an urgent problem.

"I actually started to get a little scared that day, " Song said. "More and more people started talking about it. "

Unfortunately, the Panlongcheng bridge was closed that day. "The male doctor and I don't live very close. It's half an hour's drive, an hour's drive back and forth, about fifty kilometers. But to get into the city, you have to cross the Panlongcheng Bridge. Once the bridge is closed, there is nothing I can do,"Song said, not knowing exactly how it is closed. It was his first encounter with the Panlongcheng bridge closure. The male doctor he sent to work at Treasure Pond Hospital, and once you cross the Panlongcheng Bridge, that's your destination.

"It ended up being stuck on the fact that neither of US had a pass. " Fortunately, after the doctor produced his own badge and the man in charge of closing the bridge took his temperature and had the doctor check in, he agreed to let the doctor walk across the bridge, and Song Yao's car was impassable under no circumstances.

Song photographed the closure of the Panlongcheng bridge and posted it on the Wechat Group of the car club. The group discussed it with a lot of chatter. Some drivers said it was OK to take the second and third ring roads, while others said the third ring roads had been closed.

Song Yao dare not let his parents know that he is out to drive people. Song Yao is also under pressure. Change your mask every time you send someone home, and wear at least two masks at a time. And alcohol spray before going home. By the second time, he realized that he might soon run out of masks and alcohol. And masks were among the most scarce and precious resources. At one point, the price of a pair of face masks was said to have been hyped to nearly half a gram of gold.

"The quantity can't cheat people, my mother saw our family mask these two days consumption is very big, in the heart already felt suspicious, so when eating to pretend to casually asked me, our mask is not stolen? Or did I give it away?"

Faced with a dilemma, whether to continue to pick up and see off others, Song Yao need to think.

Photos of the night scene taken by Song Yao after he gave them away

3

Song often needs to drive to work, a day to multiple locations is the norm. He bought a Harvard and drove nearly 20,000 kilometers a year. "driving is boring. It's probably an occupational hazard. "

The main reason is that Song Yao's physique has decided that he is more sensitive to this epidemic. Song Yao is very easy to catch a cold, and a cold will certainly have a fever, every time the fever to the bone seam is painful.

Since the infection of AIDS, began on time medication, Song Yao but in the heart of a firm idea: As long as the scientific effective method, do a good job of protection, infection of any disease will be very low. Whether it's aids or this new pneumonia. This seems to be a change in his attitude towards the disease after he was infected with AIDS.

On January 25, the first day of the Lunar New Year, Song Yao joined a local Wuhan HIV / AIDS Care Team wechat group. "there weren't many people in the group, but they were basically infected people who were asking for help. " This was beyond Song's imagination. "At first, I just wanted to see if I really needed something, and I could give it to them. " In fact, Song still insisted, he didn't want to get in touch with any more of his patients.

Song Yao, who had closed himself off from the world, was obstinate when he contacted the community again. On the one hand, he doesn't want to contact his patients, fearing that others will know that he is also a chronic patient who needs to take medicine, and on the other hand, he doesn't want to stay out of the way, "If I just watch, one day I need help, I'm afraid that no one will be willing to extend a hand. ". Perhaps in Song Yao's innermost heart, although does not want to change the world, but also does not want to be changed by the world, more hope can provide a little more temperature to the world.

From Jan. 25 to 27, Song transported a total of four infected people to collect medicine. "They were kids, only twenty-five or six years old, " Song said, glancing at his car as he drove. "When we got to the car, we were on our cell phones, and there wasn't much communication. "

In fact, many of the infected people who went out to get medicine under the pressure of the epidemic were people who returned from other places to Wuhan, Hubei Province for the New Year. This time the rapid closure of the city so that they must directly face the problem of obtaining medicine in another place. Most of them are younger patients, for the sudden lack of careful consideration and response to the action.

On January 26, the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention issued a notice on guaranteeing free antiretroviral drugs for people living with HIV in other places. The biggest risk is not the hassle of paperwork or the need for much documentation, but the need to break out of gated communities or villages, and the most difficult is the resistance of family members. People living with AIDS need to find a suitable excuse to protect their privacy, because isolation is temporary, and the future needs to face life is long. Once family members know that they are infected with AIDS, may be the rest of their lives to face earth-shaking changes.

During that same period, an infected patient in a village, because he immediately stopped taking his medicine, and did not want his parents to know the truth, asked the local police on the Internet if he could go to the hospital to pick up the medicine and bring it here. What he did not expect was that the police who went to deal with the case actually went straight to the parents of the patient and asked them if they knew that their child had been infected with AIDS. This time, the patient's whole person collapsed, originally just want to get drugs, but became the exposure of the disease. Do not say that this Spring Festival has no way to live, even if the next day how to face their parents, but also became the drug, but no hope of the patients to face life.

Song, aware of the risks of exposing his privacy, seemed to be a lifeline for his fellow patients. His normally unassuming Haver has become the Noah's Ark of the moment. And every time he was asked by his parents, "what are you doing out again? " He would reply carefully, "I'll be right back. I won't go far. "

The most time, Song Yao sent three patients. There was no one to talk in the little harv. "It's so depressing, it's really a special time, " Song said.

It's not just because of the outbreak that everyone's nerves are on edge. And a more important reason is that you don't have to go to the hospital to get the medicine.

On January 25, Song Yao took his patient friend to Jinyintan hospital for the first time. This time, instead of taking the Panlongcheng Bridge, he took a different route. Song stopped his car about six hundred meters from the hospital. Unexpectedly, the patient was a little upset. "Can't you drive a little further? " Song shook his head. "where can I find you when I get back? " Song said. "I'll look around for a parking space. If you get out, I'll send you a message. "

That day, Song Yao waited in the parking lot for almost an hour. When the patient finally returned, "it was almost impossible to get it. " The main reason was that almost all the medical staff had been mobilized to fight this outbreak. Getting in touch with a doctor and waiting in a hospital is a scary but necessary thing to do. However, in the follow-up several drug extraction process, Song Yao found that the hospital made adjustments in the Aids Clinic arranged on-duty Doctors.

And this patient was lucky. Another patient that Song Yao picked up went to a different hospital. After waiting for more than an hour, the patient did not get the medicine. On the return journey's vehicle, Song Yao and the patient friend all are silent, "in the heart really quite afflictive. " In Song Yao's opinion, that trip is a waste to run.

This time to send three patients, Song Yao in the departure check all the lines, almost all are closed. He had no choice but to take the Panlongcheng Bridge. When the bus stopped on this side of the bridge, the three residents were surprised to see the bridge being closed. "How do we get there? " Song said, "we have to walk. " What Song did not say was that it was the shortest distance to walk to the hospital.

Fortunately, one of the three patients, none of whom knew each other, had a pass. That's like saving two other people's lives. Otherwise, all three of them would have to get out of the car to consult with the staff, possibly using other chronic conditions, such as diabetes, as an excuse to get the staff to agree.

Photos of passes provided by volunteers of the Wuhan Gay and Lesbian Center

In fact, the chances of getting "yes" are slim. Confining people in different districts to their own districts is a step towards further improving the control of the epidemic, but it is also another challenge for patients. All Song and others can do is pick up and drop off patients.

Song Yao may not realize that when he pulled up the patients, he has given these strangers to eat a calm.

4

Song Yao is tired after all. He was used to getting out of the House with hardly any traffic, and to the occasional scream of an ambulance, but he woke up this morning feeling sick.

The day before, he had sent three of his fellow infected patients to get medicine, and on January 28, he woke up with a mild fever. It had happened to him in ordinary times. Most likely due to stress or eating unhygienic food. But this time, because of the current epidemic situation, he was somewhat worried, "It's a lie to say I'm not afraid, but I still think I've done a good job of protecting myself. I've added three layers to my face mask every time I go out, changing it every four hours. I wear goggles, and I have to alcohol myself in the basement garage before I go home, and then again before I go in the house. "If you can still get pneumonia with this kind of treatment, it just means the virus is too strong. "

By the afternoon of the same day, Song Yao had a rash on his body. He was relieved. I don't think it's new pneumonia. But the rash was not easy to endure, less than a day, Song Yao began to look for a hospital. Almost all the general hospitals in Wuhan no longer accept non-fever clinic patients, medical care and resources are invested in the fight against the epidemic. Song Yao in the Internet to find a few hospitals phone, one call in the past, finally found a not big hospital, their dermatology also received.

On those two days, the weather in Wuhan was overcast, with occasional drizzle. Song Yao was feeling a bit down. He wants two more days. First, the mask is not enough, every time out less than four more than eight masks, the family mask is less and less, parents go out to buy food also need to use. The other was that he wasn't sure whether it was a food allergy or a symptom of a strained mental state. For patients, one of the side effects of anti-hiv drugs is a rash. If you're under a lot of stress over a long period of time, the effects of the drug can also have side effects. "At least it was worth the risk, " said one volunteer driver. "I was risking my life to give it away. "

On Jan. 29, Song could no longer bear the itching caused by the rash, but none of his fellow patients asked for help. Song Yao had to go to the hospital alone. He came home from his prescription and started his medication.

Over the next few days, Song stopped picking up and dropping off patients and doctors. "since no one needed the car, it seemed like everyone had managed to get the medicine, " Song said with relief.

According to the past state, many people will return to their lives after the fifth day of the city. Most of the drugs that patients bring home will be taken on the 5th or 6th day. This time, the city, trapped in Wuhan in the patients will start around the second day of the beginning to consider how to take medicine in different places. So by the fifth day, can think of ways to get drugs of patients have been action. By January 31, even the previously discussed group of care car friends also gradually calm down.

Photos of medications provided by volunteers at the Wuhan Gay and Lesbian Center

5

On Feb. 1, Song added a caller to his wechat account. Unlike his former patients, this time it was a stranger who asked him to deliver the medicine.

Song Yao was shocked. His first reaction, as opposed to picking up and dropping off patients, was to say no, which could have been done by express delivery. In Wuhan, many communities have organized volunteer drivers since the end of January. Although the total number of volunteer drivers is only a few thousand for Wuhan, which has a population of more than 10 million, the busyness of each volunteer driver is already relieving the pressure that the city has accumulated due to the closure of the city.

But Song Yao understood that not all of his patients dared to tell the truth to the community, so he, who was also a patient friend, gained the trust of his patients invisibly, "I do not feel like a hero, just want to do a little bit of help. " Although this delivery, let him feel uncomfortable. Even if there is no express delivery, there are other ways for the two patients to pass the medicine, "but find me, I can do more and more. "

In fact, between the patient friend and the patient friend borrows medicine, is not a regular matter. First, both people should take the same combination of drugs, and second, there should be extra drugs to lend out. Such borrowing usually takes place between well-known patients and often requires a loan agreement. The agreement specifies how to borrow it and how to return it. For an infected person, the medicine is given by the day, not a single pill more. Loan out the medicine, will mean oneself will take less medicine in the future several days. Such risk shifting requires more than mere trust.

Song said he didn't want to talk too much, but he could feel his discomfort. "It's not that common anyway, and it's an epidemic period. " At the moment, his rash is still not well.

And when Song finished this "special task" , he said, the whole process is very tense. Although reporters made a variety of speculation, including whether two people have been diagnosed with new coronary pneumonia. Song Yao did not want to say more, but he carried out a more comprehensive disinfection of the car.

Song said, "listen to car friends say, recently do not allow private cars on the road, the camera shot to deduct points. " This also seems to make him more or less relaxed. These days, Song Yao's pressure is really too great, "But I still go to see my patients off. Because I'm one of them. But it's more scary to stay home every day, isn't it? It's better to do something from time to time. It's better to be sure than to be afraid and tired. "

On February 4th, another patient began asking for help. Having figured out the process of giving away people and taking medicine, Song Yao ran around again after the symptoms of the rash disappeared.

Since January 23, Song, who has been going to bed early, has been going to bed later and later. He began to give up smoking, and when he became addicted to it, he ate snacks, mostly chips. Soong began playing games more and more. "At least you can relax. "

On this day, Song Yao's mother made him a favorite food, the joy Tuo. This kind of fried food is seldom cooked at home by mother. Probably saw the pressure he was under and did it for the first time. Song Yao eat, his mother suddenly asked a sentence, "your car oil? " Song Yao thought for a while, the last lock before he also took a look, at least can drive more than 200 kilometers. And the mother asked this sentence, is she also aware of what? But Song Yao did not ask back, but to pick up the joy of the Tuo.

Song Yao had a delicious meal that day. He took a bite of the warm joy Tuo, slowly chewing, nostalgia for the taste of food in the mouth. He wanted more of these moments of happiness in his life.

That day, Song Yao drove to the outskirts of Wuhan and took his parents to the house he bought. This is also his habit of returning to Wuhan for the past two years. He spent every New Year in the house he bought. "I told my parents that the downtown area was quite lively. People in Wuhan love to be lively, " Song Yao said with a smile in his voice, "In fact, I have my own plan. Instead of going home with a few days' supply of medicine, I'll find out if I'm not careful. I'd rather be at home. My Mom and dad really don't have the habit of rummaging around. "

Chinese New Year, for people infected with AIDS, is the "clearance. ". Even if there is no epidemic this time, ordinary days, infected people have to find ways to hide the drug in the side, on time to take, not to mention home for the New Year. Even the staff of the CDC or doctors at the designated hospitals will tell us before each Chinese New Year, "Ten million more take a month's medicine, go home New Year do not know what will encounter. " But not all the infected dare to take more than half a month of medicine home. The appearance of the anti-hiv drug is hard to forget at a glance, the color of the sugar coating is rare pink, blue and yellow (the same as the color of some domestic drugs) , and the size of the pill also makes people feel puzzled, what medicine can be bigger than the good store piece even on a circle? While half a month's supply is more than enough for a simple vitamin pill bottle, no infected person is willing to take such a risk, leaving family members with unnecessary doubts and endless trouble to follow up.

"Too many drugs, it is easy to be found, " said one person who declined to give his name and address. The patient came back to Wuhan from Northeast China for the Spring Festival. He brought only seven days' worth of medicine with him. "It was expected that he would be back at the latest on the sixth day of the Lunar New Year. " But he did not expect that after the order to close the city of Wuhan on January 23 was issued, "The train station, the highway, the airport are not immediately closed, incredibly still have a few hours to leave! " In his view, this is a silver lining.

Shortly after 6 a.m. on Jan. 23, he said to his parents, "I have to go. " His parents objected, "it's just a city shutdown. Why are you panicking? There are so many New Year's items in the family, and you have food and drink, so you can stay in Wuhan. "

If not infected with AIDS, he would have stayed, "but now is not the same ah! The drug is life. I stay, once the drug ran out, life is gone. "

The road out of Wuhan is not easy. The patient could not buy a direct flight back to the northeast, and he was afraid to go to a first-tier city like Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Shenzhen. "None of us had any symptoms. " But he was still nervous. first-tier cities must be strictly controlled, so he decided to book a high-speed train ticket from Wuhan to Nanjing, and then from Nanjing back to the northeast. Instead, he found a self-driving car from Wuhan to Nanjing. "I even wanted to go to Henan, but luckily I found a car to Nanjing. "

The patient friend has been urging the owner to pick him up a little faster, while his parents at the last moment to see his son's insistence, agreed, although do not understand why this is.

It was not the first time that a patient had been away on New Year's Day, but it was the first time he had left home less than a day before the Spring Festival. "It wasn't until I got on the highway that I was relieved, but my mom kept calling me, and I kept telling myself not to cry. " When I got back, the patient was in a state of self-isolation, and everything was fine.

And many of those infected are not as clean as this patient. In Wuhan, a sprawling city on the new frontier, many people have canceled their plans to go home for the New Year and are returning tickets, buying new year goods and adapting to life with fewer and fewer cars on the streets.

For many chronic patients, the suspension of public transportation and isolation at home means that once the drugs in hand to control the disease run out, they face withdrawal and withdrawal, and the consequences are not as simple as not getting the disease under control, more likely means the failure of the drug, drug resistance.

Such chronic diseases include many kinds, AIDS is one of them. For people living with AIDS, drug resistance may mean that a certain or even a certain series of, the same pharmacological drug failure. This combination of drugs on the original choice is not much AIDS patients, like a gun to the temple.

Over the next few days, Song felt lucky. On my way to pick up mom and dad, I stopped by a pharmacy on the outskirts of town, and I went in and bought six bags of disposable surgical masks. And then, about a week ago, he went to Wuhan State Hospital to pick up his medicine.

"The city was closed at the beginning, and it was not easy to stay at home all day. " Shortly before 10 p.m. on January 23, Song received a message from a friend of a colleague asking for help, "It was a female doctor, a few years younger than me, and the hospital asked them to return to their posts urgently, but there was no taxi, Didi or anything like that. " The city had fallen into a strange silence. Lights are on in every home, almost everyone is waiting in front of the television, more and more medical staff have become "retrograde. ".

The lady doctor's home is in Hankou. The drive from Panlongcheng to Hankou, which normally takes 40 or 50 minutes, was an excruciatingly slow half-hour. Song Yao originally more introverted silence, in the face of female doctors, do not know what to say. The woman doctor has been answering messages on her cell phone, saying she's on her way to the hospital. Soong drove for another half hour to take the woman to the hospital. Before getting off the bus, the female doctor told Song Yao, "the mask should be changed regularly, and you should wear goggles! " After returning home, Song Yao's heart was quite proud, "It never occurred to me that an hiv-infected person like myself would one day be able to go to the doctor and contribute to the hospital. "

As song parked his car in an underground garage and headed upstairs to his home, he had no idea that he would need to pick up and drop off members of his aids-infected community over the next few days. Song prefers to refer to them as "sick friends. " "In the past, I didn't know any of them. I didn't want to know them, and I didn't want anyone to know that I had the disease. "

On the advice of a female doctor, Song drove to a still open sports equipment the next day and bought three goggles for the family, each costing 199 yuan. Less than an hour after returning home in the afternoon, he received a call from a doctor recommended by a friend. "Can you take me to the hospital? " Song Yao was a little surprised. He did not expect the doctors in Wuhan to face the city is also so helpless, even if want to go to the hospital to work, also can not ride a bicycle to Wuhan, after all, is a mountainous area. But when the most basic traffic is not able to guarantee, how to arrive at the scene, has become a real problem. In fact, the follow-up trip to the public has become an urgent problem.

"I actually started to get a little scared that day, " Song said. "More and more people started talking about it. "

Unfortunately, the Panlongcheng bridge was closed that day. "The male doctor and I don't live very close. It's half an hour's drive, an hour's drive back and forth, about fifty kilometers. But to get into the city, you have to cross the Panlongcheng Bridge. Once the bridge is closed, there is nothing I can do,"Song said, not knowing exactly how it is closed. It was his first encounter with the Panlongcheng bridge closure. The male doctor he sent to work at Treasure Pond Hospital, and once you cross the Panlongcheng Bridge, that's your destination.

"It ended up being stuck on the fact that neither of US had a pass. " Fortunately, after the doctor produced his own badge and the man in charge of closing the bridge took his temperature and had the doctor check in, he agreed to let the doctor walk across the bridge, and Song Yao's car was impassable under no circumstances.

Song photographed the closure of the Panlongcheng bridge and posted it on the Wechat Group of the car club. The group discussed it with a lot of chatter. Some drivers said it was OK to take the second and third ring roads, while others said the third ring roads had been closed.

Song Yao dare not let his parents know that he is out to drive people. Song Yao is also under pressure. Change your mask every time you send someone home, and wear at least two masks at a time. And alcohol spray before going home. By the second time, he realized that he might soon run out of masks and alcohol. And masks were among the most scarce and precious resources. At one point, the price of a pair of face masks was said to have been hyped to nearly half a gram of gold.

"The quantity can't cheat people, my mother saw our family mask these two days consumption is very big, in the heart already felt suspicious, so when eating to pretend to casually asked me, our mask is not stolen? Or did I give it away?"

Faced with a dilemma, whether to continue to pick up and see off others, Song Yao need to think.

Song often needs to drive to work, a day to multiple locations is the norm. He bought a Harvard and drove nearly 20,000 kilometers a year. "driving is boring. It's probably an occupational hazard. "

The main reason is that Song Yao's physique has decided that he is more sensitive to this epidemic. Song Yao is very easy to catch a cold, and a cold will certainly have a fever, every time the fever to the bone seam is painful.

Since the infection of AIDS, began on time medication, Song Yao but in the heart of a firm idea: As long as the scientific effective method, do a good job of protection, infection of any disease will be very low. Whether it's aids or this new pneumonia. This seems to be a change in his attitude towards the disease after he was infected with AIDS.

On January 25, the first day of the Lunar New Year, Song Yao joined a local Wuhan HIV / AIDS Care Team wechat group. "there weren't many people in the group, but they were basically infected people who were asking for help. " This was beyond Song's imagination. "At first, I just wanted to see if I really needed something, and I could give it to them. " In fact, Song still insisted, he didn't want to get in touch with any more of his patients.

Song Yao, who had closed himself off from the world, was obstinate when he contacted the community again. On the one hand, he doesn't want to contact his patients, fearing that others will know that he is also a chronic patient who needs to take medicine, and on the other hand, he doesn't want to stay out of the way, "If I just watch, one day I need help, I'm afraid that no one will be willing to extend a hand. ". Perhaps in Song Yao's innermost heart, although does not want to change the world, but also does not want to be changed by the world, more hope can provide a little more temperature to the world.

From Jan. 25 to 27, Song transported a total of four infected people to collect medicine. "They were kids, only twenty-five or six years old, " Song said, glancing at his car as he drove. "When we got to the car, we were on our cell phones, and there wasn't much communication. "

In fact, many of the infected people who went out to get medicine under the pressure of the epidemic were people who returned from other places to Wuhan, Hubei Province for the New Year. This time the rapid closure of the city so that they must directly face the problem of obtaining medicine in another place. Most of them are younger patients, for the sudden lack of careful consideration and response to the action.

On January 26, the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention issued a notice on guaranteeing free antiretroviral drugs for people living with HIV in other places. The biggest risk is not the hassle of paperwork or the need for much documentation, but the need to break out of gated communities or villages, and the most difficult is the resistance of family members. People living with AIDS need to find a suitable excuse to protect their privacy, because isolation is temporary, and the future needs to face life is long. Once family members know that they are infected with AIDS, may be the rest of their lives to face earth-shaking changes.

During that same period, an infected patient in a village, because he immediately stopped taking his medicine, and did not want his parents to know the truth, asked the local police on the Internet if he could go to the hospital to pick up the medicine and bring it here. What he did not expect was that the police who went to deal with the case actually went straight to the parents of the patient and asked them if they knew that their child had been infected with AIDS. This time, the patient's whole person collapsed, originally just want to get drugs, but became the exposure of the disease. Do not say that this Spring Festival has no way to live, even if the next day how to face their parents, but also became the drug, but no hope of the patients to face life.

Song, aware of the risks of exposing his privacy, seemed to be a lifeline for his fellow patients. His normally unassuming Haver has become the Noah's Ark of the moment. And every time he was asked by his parents, "what are you doing out again? " He would reply carefully, "I'll be right back. I won't go far. "

The most time, Song Yao sent three patients. There was no one to talk in the little harv. "It's so depressing, it's really a special time, " Song said.

It's not just because of the outbreak that everyone's nerves are on edge. And a more important reason is that you don't have to go to the hospital to get the medicine.

On January 25, Song Yao took his patient friend to Jinyintan hospital for the first time. This time, instead of taking the Panlongcheng Bridge, he took a different route. Song stopped his car about six hundred meters from the hospital. Unexpectedly, the patient was a little upset. "Can't you drive a little further? " Song shook his head. "where can I find you when I get back? " Song said. "I'll look around for a parking space. If you get out, I'll send you a message. "

That day, Song Yao waited in the parking lot for almost an hour. When the patient finally returned, "it was almost impossible to get it. " The main reason was that almost all the medical staff had been mobilized to fight this outbreak. Getting in touch with a doctor and waiting in a hospital is a scary but necessary thing to do. However, in the follow-up several drug extraction process, Song Yao found that the hospital made adjustments in the Aids Clinic arranged on-duty Doctors.

And this patient was lucky. Another patient that Song Yao picked up went to a different hospital. After waiting for more than an hour, the patient did not get the medicine. On the return journey's vehicle, Song Yao and the patient friend all are silent, "in the heart really quite afflictive. " In Song Yao's opinion, that trip is a waste to run.

This time to send three patients, Song Yao in the departure check all the lines, almost all are closed. He had no choice but to take the Panlongcheng Bridge. When the bus stopped on this side of the bridge, the three residents were surprised to see the bridge being closed. "How do we get there? " Song said, "we have to walk. " What Song did not say was that it was the shortest distance to walk to the hospital.

Fortunately, one of the three patients, none of whom knew each other, had a pass. That's like saving two other people's lives. Otherwise, all three of them would have to get out of the car to consult with the staff, possibly using other chronic conditions, such as diabetes, as an excuse to get the staff to agree.

Song Yao is tired after all. He was used to getting out of the House with hardly any traffic, and to the occasional scream of an ambulance, but he woke up this morning feeling sick.

The day before, he had sent three of his fellow infected patients to get medicine, and on January 28, he woke up with a mild fever. It had happened to him in ordinary times. Most likely due to stress or eating unhygienic food. But this time, because of the current epidemic situation, he was somewhat worried, "It's a lie to say I'm not afraid, but I still think I've done a good job of protecting myself. I've added three layers to my face mask every time I go out, changing it every four hours. I wear goggles, and I have to alcohol myself in the basement garage before I go home, and then again before I go in the house. "If you can still get pneumonia with this kind of treatment, it just means the virus is too strong. "

By the afternoon of the same day, Song Yao had a rash on his body. He was relieved. I don't think it's new pneumonia. But the rash was not easy to endure, less than a day, Song Yao began to look for a hospital. Almost all the general hospitals in Wuhan no longer accept non-fever clinic patients, medical care and resources are invested in the fight against the epidemic. Song Yao in the Internet to find a few hospitals phone, one call in the past, finally found a not big hospital, their dermatology also received.

On those two days, the weather in Wuhan was overcast, with occasional drizzle. Song Yao was feeling a bit down. He wants two more days. First, the mask is not enough, every time out less than four more than eight masks, the family mask is less and less, parents go out to buy food also need to use. The other was that he wasn't sure whether it was a food allergy or a symptom of a strained mental state. For patients, one of the side effects of anti-hiv drugs is a rash. If you're under a lot of stress over a long period of time, the effects of the drug can also have side effects. "At least it was worth the risk, " said one volunteer driver. "I was risking my life to give it away. "

Over the next few days, Song stopped picking up and dropping off patients and doctors. "since no one needed the car, it seemed like everyone had managed to get the medicine, " Song said with relief.

According to the past state, many people will return to their lives after the fifth day of the city. Most of the drugs that patients bring home will be taken on the 5th or 6th day. This time, the city, trapped in Wuhan in the patients will start around the second day of the beginning to consider how to take medicine in different places. So by the fifth day, can think of ways to get drugs of patients have been action. By January 31, even the previously discussed group of care car friends also gradually calm down.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photos of medications provided by volunteers at the Wuhan Gay and Lesbian Center

5

On Feb. 1, Song added a caller to his wechat account. Unlike his former patients, this time it was a stranger who asked him to deliver the medicine.

Song Yao was shocked. His first reaction, as opposed to picking up and dropping off patients, was to say no, which could have been done by express delivery. In Wuhan, many communities have organized volunteer drivers since the end of January. Although the total number of volunteer drivers is only a few thousand for Wuhan, which has a population of more than 10 million, the busyness of each volunteer driver is already relieving the pressure that the city has accumulated due to the closure of the city.

But Song Yao understood that not all of his patients dared to tell the truth to the community, so he, who was also a patient friend, gained the trust of his patients invisibly, "I do not feel like a hero, just want to do a little bit of help. " Although this delivery, let him feel uncomfortable. Even if there is no express delivery, there are other ways for the two patients to pass the medicine, "but find me, I can do more and more. "

In fact, between the patient friend and the patient friend borrows medicine, is not a regular matter. First, both people should take the same combination of drugs, and second, there should be extra drugs to lend out. Such borrowing usually takes place between well-known patients and often requires a loan agreement. The agreement specifies how to borrow it and how to return it. For an infected person, the medicine is given by the day, not a single pill more. Loan out the medicine, will mean oneself will take less medicine in the future several days. Such risk shifting requires more than mere trust.

Song said he didn't want to talk too much, but he could feel his discomfort. "It's not that common anyway, and it's an epidemic period. " At the moment, his rash is still not well.

And when Song finished this "special task" , he said, the whole process is very tense. Although reporters made a variety of speculation, including whether two people have been diagnosed with new coronary pneumonia. Song Yao did not want to say more, but he carried out a more comprehensive disinfection of the car.

Song said, "listen to car friends say, recently do not allow private cars on the road, the camera shot to deduct points. " This also seems to make him more or less relaxed. These days, Song Yao's pressure is really too great, "But I still go to see my patients off. Because I'm one of them. But it's more scary to stay home every day, isn't it? It's better to do something from time to time. It's better to be sure than to be afraid and tired. "

On February 4th, another patient began asking for help. Having figured out the process of giving away people and taking medicine, Song Yao ran around again after the symptoms of the rash disappeared.

Since January 23, Song, who has been going to bed early, has been going to bed later and later. He began to give up smoking, and when he became addicted to it, he ate snacks, mostly chips. Soong began playing games more and more. "At least you can relax. "

On this day, Song Yao's mother made him a favorite food, the joy Tuo. This kind of fried food is seldom cooked at home by mother. Probably saw the pressure he was under and did it for the first time. Song Yao eat, his mother suddenly asked a sentence, "your car oil? " Song Yao thought for a while, the last lock before he also took a look, at least can drive more than 200 kilometers. And the mother asked this sentence, is she also aware of what? But Song Yao did not ask back, but to pick up the joy of the Tuo.

Song Yao had a delicious meal that day. He took a bite of the warm joy Tuo, slowly chewing, nostalgia for the taste of food in the mouth. He wanted more of these moments of happiness in his life.
